\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marianne Vos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Vos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Vos\"}, {\"begin\": 4132, \"end\": 4147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pfeiffer_Georgi\", \"score\": 0.9999994495557681, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pfeiffer Georgi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pfeiffer_Georgi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pfeiffer_Georgi\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a race\", \"from\": 4000, \"to\": 4006}, {\"ngram\": \"attacks\", \"from\": 4040, \"to\": 4047}, {\"ngram\": \"a select group\", \"from\": 4055, \"to\": 4069}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 4073, \"to\": 4079}, {\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 4091, \"to\": 4098}, {\"ngram\": \"a handful\", \"from\": 4166, \"to\": 4175}, {\"ngram\": \"pav\\u00e9 sectors\", \"from\": 4179, \"to\": 4191}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Six riders arrived at the velodrome, and Kopecky was the last to launch her sprint.\", \"from\": 4204, \"to\": 4287, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Six riders\", \"from\": 4204, \"to\": 4214}, {\"ngram\": \"the velodrome\", \"from\": 4226, \"to\": 4239}, {\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 4245, \"to\": 4252}, {\"ngram\": \"her sprint\", \"from\": 4276, \"to\": 4286}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Belgian - resplendent in an all-white rainbow kit - timed her sprint to perfection, navigating her way around the outside group at the perfect moment to confirm her place as Queen of the Classics.\", \"from\": 4288, \"to\": 4488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4292, \"end\": 4299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.631373160054418e-18, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 4479, \"end\": 4487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.869622157126948e-180, \"text\": \"Classics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an all-white rainbow kit\", \"from\": 4317, \"to\": 4341}, {\"ngram\": \"her sprint\", \"from\": 4350, \"to\": 4360}, {\"ngram\": \"perfection\", \"from\": 4364, \"to\": 4374}, {\"ngram\": \"her way\", \"from\": 4387, \"to\": 4394}, {\"ngram\": \"the outside group\", \"from\": 4402, \"to\": 4419}, {\"ngram\": \"the perfect moment\", \"from\": 4423, \"to\": 4441}, {\"ngram\": \"her place\", \"from\": 4453, \"to\": 4462}, {\"ngram\": \"Queen\", \"from\": 4466, \"to\": 4471}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just 24 hours later, a week afterclinching a third Tour of Flanders title, Van der Poel delivered an equally powerful display in northern France.\", \"from\": 4490, \"to\": 4635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4628, \"end\": 4634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999994597601, \"rank\": 5.383128365799838e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a week\", \"from\": 4511, \"to\": 4517}, {\"ngram\": \"a third Tour\", \"from\": 4533, \"to\": 4545}, {\"ngram\": \"Flanders title\", \"from\": 4549, \"to\": 4563}, {\"ngram\": \"Van der\", \"from\": 4565, \"to\": 4572}, {\"ngram\": \"Poel\", \"from\": 4573, \"to\": 4577}, {\"ngram\": \"an equally powerful display\", \"from\": 4588, \"to\": 4615}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Kopecky's decisive move came inside the final 100m, the Dutchman made his key attack with 60km to go.\", \"from\": 4637, \"to\": 4744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4699, \"end\": 4707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.547191892537326e-14, \"text\": \"Dutchman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kopecky's decisive move\", \"from\": 4643, \"to\": 4666}, {\"ngram\": \"the final 100m\", \"from\": 4679, \"to\": 4693}, {\"ngram\": \"his key attack\", \"from\": 4713, \"to\": 4727}, {\"ngram\": \"60km\", \"from\": 4733, \"to\": 4737}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Benefiting from smart teamwork by his teammates Gianni Vermeersch and Jasper Philipsen, he powered away from the rest of the peloton and would not be seen again.\", \"from\": 4745, \"to\": 4906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4793, \"end\": 4810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gianni_Vermeersch\", \"score\": 0.9999981433756102, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gianni Vermeersch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gianni_Vermeersch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gianni_Vermeersch\"}, {\"begin\": 4815, \"end\": 4831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasper_Philipsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jasper Philipsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasper_Philipsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasper_Philipsen\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"smart teamwork\", \"from\": 4761, \"to\": 4775}, {\"ngram\": \"his teammates\", \"from\": 4779, \"to\": 4792}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 4854, \"to\": 4862}, {\"ngram\": \"the peloton\", \"from\": 4866, \"to\": 4877}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The time difference between MVDP and the second finisher, his teammate Philipsen, would eventually be three minutes, breaking the record for the fastest edition of L'Enfer du Nord in its 128-year history, and becoming the first rider in 11 years to complete the Flanders-Roubaix double.\", \"from\": 4908, \"to\": 5194, \"entities\": [{\"begin